        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 3:41AM CDT by NWS Hastings NE</headline>
        <description>At 340 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Shelby, or 16 miles west of David City, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Shelby around 345 AM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
